Class EarthServerGenericClient.AbstractSceneModel

Abstract base class for scene models.
Defined in: Module_Base.js.

EarthServerGenericClient.AbstractSceneModel()
Field Detail
bindings
All objects that are bound to the module. The will be noticed if the models is moved or altered. Example: Annotation layers should be moved with the module and change the height when the elevation changes.
imageFormat
The used Image format (if one is used)
Default Value:
"png"
name
Name of the model. This will be display in the UI.
Default Value:
Name is given by the module
receivedDataCount
The amount of already received responses. Along with requests this is used to keep track of the loading progress.
Default Value:
0
requests
The amount of requests the model do. It is needed to keep track of the loading progress.
Default Value:
1
sidePanels
Flag if side panels should be added to the terrain.
Default Value:
false

The Transparency of the model.
Default Value:
0

Method Detail
addBinding(bindingObject)
Adds an Object that will be informed about movements and alterations of the model.
Parameters:
bindingObject
- Object that will receive the notification.
{boolean} checkReceivedData(data)
Validates the received data from the server request. Checks if a texture and a heightmap are available at the moment.
Parameters:
data
- Received data from the server request.
Returns:
{boolean} - TRUE if OK, FALSE if some data is missing
createPlaceHolder()
This creates a placeholder Element for the model. It consists of an simple quad. Models that use this placeholder should remove it of course.
{Element} createTransform(xRes, yRes, zRes, minvalue)
Creates the transform for the scene model to fit into the fishtank/cube. This is done automatically by the scene model.
Parameters:
xRes
- Size of the received data on the x-axis (e.g. the requested DEM )
yRes
- Size of the received data on the y-axis
zRes
- Size of the received data on the z-axis
minvalue
- Minimum Value along the y-axis (e.g. minimum value in a DEM, so the model starts at it's wished location)
Returns:
{Element}
elevationUpdateBinding(value)
This function calls every binding object that the elevation of the models was changed.
Parameters:
value
- This is the value the that was given to SceneManager::updateElevation().
{{}} getAreaOfInterest()
Returns object with the area of interest of the model. (minx,miny,maxx,maxy)
Returns:
{{}}
{float} getDemNoDataValue()
Returns the noData Value for the DEM or undefined if not set.
Returns:
{float}
{number} getDemValueAt3DPosition(xPos, zPos)
Returns the dem value of it's terrain at a specific point in the 3D scene.
Parameters:
xPos
- Position on the x-axis.
zPos
- Position on the z-axis.
Returns:
{number} - The height of the dem.
{number} getHeightAt3DPosition(xPos, zPos)
Returns the elevation value of it's terrain at a specific point in the 3D scene.
Parameters:
xPos
- Position on the x-axis.
zPos
- Position on the z-axis.
Returns:
{number} - The height on the y-axis.
{String} getName()
Returns the name of the model.
Returns:
{String}
movementUpdateBindings(movementType, value)
This function is called if the model is moved in the scene. All bindings will also get the movement update.
Parameters:
movementType
- Type of the movement: xAxis,zAxis,elevation...
value
- Updated position
removeBinding(bindingObject)
Removes an Object that will be informed about movements and alterations of the model.
Parameters:
bindingObject
- Object that will no longer receive the notification.
removePlaceHolder()
Removes the PlaceHolder created in createPlaceHolder(). If already deleted nothing happens.
{String} replaceSymbolsInString(inputString)
Replaces all $xx symbols with the value-
Parameters:
inputString
- Input WCPS query string.
Returns:
{String} - String with symbols replaced by values.
reportProgress()
Modules report their loading progress with this function which reports to the main scene.
setAreaOfInterest(minx, miny, maxx, maxy)
Sets the area of interest for the model. (Lower Corner, Upper Corner)
Parameters:
minx
- Minimum/Lower Latitude
miny
- Minimum/Lower Longitude
maxx
- Maximum/Upper Latitude
maxy
- Maximum/Upper Longitude
setDefaults()
Sets the default values. This is done automatically by the scene model.
setDemNoDataValue(value)
Sets the DEM value to be considered as NODATA in the DEM. No Faces will be drawn having a vertex with that value.
Parameters:
value
- No data value
setHeightResolution(value)
Sets the height resolution of the model. This effects the scaling of the elevation of the model. The parameter should be the difference between the smallest and biggest value of the DEM. Make the sure the value fits to the model's size.
Parameters:
value
setImageFormat(imageFormat)
Sets the image format for the server request.
Parameters:
imageFormat
- Default "png".
setName(modelName)
Sets the name of the scene model.
Parameters:
modelName
- Name of the model.
setOffset(xOffset, yOffset, zOffset)
Sets the position of the scene model within the fishtank/cube. Values between [0-1]
Parameters:
xOffset
- Offset on the x-axis/width Default:0
yOffset
- Offset on the y-axis/height Default:0
zOffset
- Offset on the z-axis/depth Default:0
setResolution(xRes, zRes)
Sets the resolution of the scene model (if possible).
Parameters:
xRes
- Resolution on the x-axis/Latitude
zRes
- Resolution on the z-axis/Longitude
setScale(xScale, yScale, zScale)
Sets the size of the scene model compared to the fishtank/cube. Values between 0 - 1.
Parameters:
xScale
- Size of the model on the x-axis/width Default:1 (whole cube)
yScale
- Size of the model on the y-axis/height Default:0.3 (30% of the cube)
zScale
- Size of the model on the x-axis/width Default:1 (whole cube)
setSidePanels(value)
Sets if side panels should be added to the model.
Parameters:
value
setSidePanelsImageLinks(links)
Sets the queries for the four side panels' textures.
Parameters:
links
- Array with four image links.
setTextureNoDataValue(red, green, blue)
Sets the RGB value to be considered as NODATA in the TEXTURE. All pixels with this RGB value will be drawn transparent.
Parameters:
red
- Value for the red channel.
green
- Value for the green channel.
blue
- Value for the blue channel.
setTransparency(transparency)
Sets the initial transparency of the scene model. The function accepts a parameter value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
Parameters:
transparency
- Value of transparency.
updateTransparency(transparency)
Updates the transparency during runtime of the scene model. The function accepts a value in the range of 0 (fully opaque) and 1(fully transparent).
Parameters:
transparency
- Value of transparency.
